    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Aryl bromides are organic compounds containing a bromine atom directly bonded to an aromatic ring. The general structure of an aryl bromide is represented as $\\mathrm{Ar}-\\mathrm{Br}$, where \"Ar\" denotes an aryl group, which is a functional group derived from an aromatic ring (such as benzene or naphthalene) by the removal of one hydrogen atom.</p>\n<p>M-is not aryl, O does not have Br directly connected to benzene.</p>",
